          <controlProperties>
            <text>Is%20there%20any%20sort%20of%20historical%20precendent%20for%20this%20kind%20of%20prize%3F%20%0A%20%0APrizes%20have%20been%20used%20to%20incentivize%20a%20number%20of%20feats%20in%20science%20and%20engineering.%20%20For%20example%2C%20In%201795%2C%20Napoleon%27s%20government%20offered%20a%20prize%20of%2012%2C000%20francs%20for%20a%20method%20of%20preserving%20food%2C%20suitable%20for%20use%20by%20the%20French%20army.%20%20In%201810%2C%20Chef%20Nicolas%20Appert%20was%20awarded%20the%20prize%20for%20his%20method%20of%20packing%20food%20in%20bottles%2C%20corking%20them%2C%20and%20submerging%20them%20in%20boiling%20water%20to%20stop%20spoilage.%20%20%0A%20%0AThe%20Orteig%20Prize%20was%20a%20%2425%2C000%20reward%20offered%20on%20May%2019%2C%201919%2C%20by%20New%20York%20hotel%20owner%20Raymond%20Orteig%20to%20the%20first%20aviator%28s%29%20to%20fly%20non-stop%20from%20New%20York%20City%20to%20Paris%20or%20vice-versa.%20%20Several%20famous%20aviators%20made%20unsuccessful%20attempts%20at%20the%20New%20York%u2013Paris%20flight%20before%20Charles%20Lindbergh%20won%20the%20prize%20in%201927%20in%20his%20aircraft%20Spirit%20of%20St.%20Louis.%0A%20%0AMore%20recently%2C%20the%20Ansari%20X%20Prize%20was%20a%20US%2410%2C000%2C000%20prize%20for%20the%20first%20non-government%20organization%20to%20launch%20a%20reusable%20manned%20spacecraft%20into%20space%20twice%20within%20two%20weeks.%20%20The%20prize%20was%20won%20on%20October%204%2C%202004%20by%20the%20Tier%20One%20project%20designed%20by%20Burt%20Rutan%20and%20financed%20by%20Microsoft%20co-founder%20Paul%20Allen%2C%20using%20the%20experimental%20spaceplane%20SpaceShipOne.</text>
